{
  "doc_id": "38489",
  "text": "On CT imaging, bladder diverticulitis usually manifests as mucosal enhancement with infiltration of the periverticular fat, as seen in this case [CITATION_1] . Increased FDG uptake in the diverticular wall and surrounding fat may also be seen on PET imaging; however, due to the intense activity of FDG excreted in the urinary bladder and blooming artifacts, evaluation of FDG uptake in the bladder wall and surrounding fat is limited (9).",
